@node Introduction "Introduction"

@{b}@{u}Introduction:@{uu}@{ub}

Welcome to @{fg shine}AKIconzGold@{fg text}!

After having released 4 @{"collections" link Others} of (mostly games) icons using the
standard MagicWB colours @{"I" link Author} got bored of them. After seeing more and
more people using the more colourful New- or even GlowIcons @{"I" link Author} looked
over my simple 8 col. WB and decided to do something against it! ;-)

So @{"I" link Author} was looking for possibilities to have a more @{"colourful WB" system "SYS:Utilities/Multiview SCREEN WB-Screenshot"} but
without "OS 3.1 non-standard" stuff as NewIcons or GlowIcons.

First @{"I" link Author} discovered the RomIcons and later the BNSMWBicons on Aminet
and thought:

 "WOW! They are looking great! Using a @{"pre-defined 32-col. palette" link Installation}
  you could get such colourful (standard!) icons @{"I" link Author} never expected!".

Together with FBlit, which even makes a 32 col. DblPAL HiRes flickerfree
screen work well on a 030/50 and without a gfx card this was the optimal
solution in my eyes.

And so the re-built of the whole icons and patterns scheme on my HD
begun ...

After the existing icons did not cover all my needs @{"I" link Author} begun to create
more and more by myself - and here are the first results ...

@{" « Back " link Main}

@endnode

@node Description "Description"

@{b}@{u}Description:@{uu}@{ub}

This is a collection of 16-/32-coloured icons in the BNSMWBicons style.
As these icons, mine use the 8 MWB colours, expanded by the 8 RomIcons
colours and again expanded by 13 more colours introduced with the 7th
and corrected with the 8th release of the BNSMWBicons on Aminet.

@{b}For correct look the icons need a screen with 32 or more colours and
a pre-defined @{"32-colour palette" link Installation} for the Workbench.@{ub}

With this palette @{fg shine}all your icons will have the right colours@{fg text} and so
will look well:
 - the original 8-colour MagicWB icons (anyone knows them!)
 - the 16-colour RomIcons (often found in the installers of WHDLoad/jst)
 - the 32-colour BNSMWBicons and so the @{fg shine}AKIconzGold@{fg text} as well ;-)
 - NewIcons (as the palette is using a wide-spread range of colours)
 - and even GlowIcons will look relatively nice on a 32-col. screen
   (although you'll use a more colourful screenmode for them anyway...)

@{fg shine}So if you don't want to restrict yourself to one sort of icons but always
want to have the right colour settings for any icons, you should set this
palette!@{fg text}

There are @{fg shine}300@{fg text} icons for different apps, games (both incl. drawers),
prefs, WBStartup tools and so on inside this collection.

